Package com.eatthepath.jeospatial.util

Provides simple implementations of the GeospatialPoint interface and Comparators and utility classes for conducting nearest-neighbor searches in GeospatialPointDatabases.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
CachingGeospatialPoint A caching geospatial point is an extension of a simple geospatial point that trades memory efficiency for processing time in calculating distance to other points.
GeospatialDistanceComparator<T extends GeospatialPoint> A comparator that sorts geospatial points in order of increasing distance from a given origin point.
ReverseComparator<T> A Comparator that reverse the sorting order imposed by another Comparator.
SearchResults<E extends GeospatialPoint> The @{code SearchResults} class is a fixed-size PriorityQueue subclass that may or may not accept points that are offered to it based on several criteria.
SimpleGeospatialPoint A simple geospatial point implementation.
 

Package com.eatthepath.jeospatial.util Description
